1) Input & Clarification
As a user, I want to enter unstructured ideas so that I can organize my thoughts easily.
As a user, I want to answer clarification questions so that the system better understands my intent.

2) Mind Map Generation
As a user, I want the system to break my idea into phases so that I get a clear roadmap.
As a user, I want my idea to be converted into a structured hierarchy so that it is easy to understand.
As a user, I want the system to validate the generated structure so that I receive correct output.
As a user, I want enhanced visualization (colors, emojis, summaries) so that my mind map is more readable.

3) Visualization & Interaction
As a user, I want to view my mind map visually so that I can explore relationships between ideas.
As a user, I want an interactive diagram so that I can navigate large structures easily.

4) Export & Sharing
As a user, I want to download my mind map as PNG so that I can share it as an image.
As a user, I want to export my mind map as PDF.
As a user, I want to export JSON so that I can reuse the structure programmatically.

5) Performance & Reliability
As a user, I want fast responses so that I don’t have to wait long.
As a user, I want the system to handle invalid or empty input so that I don’t face errors.
As a user, I want to refine my input multiple times so that I can improve the output quality.
As a user, I want consistent results so that I can rely on the system for repeated use.